Notes_siteFormat: each site is a full 50-stop BBS route
Notes_spFormat: waterbirds and nocturnal birds had previously been filtered out
Notes_countFormat: Data represents number of individuals seen over 50 3-min point counts
Notes_timeFormat: Each site sampled once annually during the breeding season

Notes_siteFormat: Only one site in this dataset. The site name gives information on sample method. No changes made.
Notes_spFormat: several species removed. Firstly, there were a few instances where a an entry was not identified down enough to be distinguished from other entries. For example, if one entry is only specified to the genus, but there are other entries of that genus that are narrowed down to the species, there is a possibility for overlap. Entries with uncertain species marked with cf. were renamed into "Genus sp." if there were multiple of those entries. Changed one entry that identified the organism to the form, which is more than specific than species, to just the species.
Notes_countFormat: Data represents count. No changes made
Notes_timeFormat: temporal data provided as years, only modification was converting to a numeric object

Notes_siteFormat: no site information available here.  All sites are listed as censusbreedingbirds_Neotoma.  May need to get data again or re-check source.
Notes_spFormat: all species good, none removed from data
Notes_countFormat: Data represents abundance counts. no changes or removals necessary
Notes_timeFormat: data provided as years. only modification to this field was converting to numeric object.

Notes_siteFormat: SampleID column from raw dataset just contains the year sampled. There is only one site for this dataset, so all site column entries were changed to "Skokholm
Notes_spFormat: No species removed.
Notes_countFormat: Data represents count. There were no NAs nor 0s that required removal
Notes_timeFormat: temporal data provided as years. Only modification was converting it to numerical object

Notes_siteFormat: site data included two sites followed by year: Redvers_year and Lousana_year.  Used substring to remove the year from the site leaving just the site in the data.
Notes_spFormat: all species good, none removed from data
Notes_countFormat: Data represents abundance counts. no changes or removals necessary
Notes_timeFormat: data provided as years. only modification to this field was converting to numeric object.

Notes_siteFormat: sites were listed as South_Africa_lat_long, so I used substring to remove the South Africa text, leaving only lat_long data. No changes or removals were made to the actual data.
Notes_spFormat: Removed several species entries because they did not reference recognizable species: LESSER-CRESTED_X_SAND and KERMADEC_X_ROUND_ISLA. There were many entries that were cut off in the original dataset. These were renamed to their full names. For example: PACHYPTILA_CRASSIROST was replaced with PACHYPTILA_CRASSIROSTRIS
Notes_countFormat: Data represents abundance. no changes or removals necessary
Notes_timeFormat: temporal data provided yearly. only change made was to a numeric object.

Notes_siteFormat: data includes only one site: Belgium. No changes made
Notes_spFormat: all species good, none removed from data
Notes_countFormat: Data represents cover. There were no NAs nor 0s that required removal
Notes_timeFormat: temporal data provided as years. The only modification to this field involved converting to a numeric object.

Notes_siteFormat: Sites have a lot of unnecessary information including species names, catch methods, etc. No changes made to site data, need to find way to remove some unwanted info from sites
Notes_spFormat: several entries were removed or changed because they were only identified to the genus, with other entries of that genus being identified to the species. This means that those entries could possibly fall under the other identified species entries. One typo was found and changed:  TH+M37663ALASSIOSIRA_ANTARCTICA_BOREALIS
Notes_countFormat: Data represents count. There were no NAs nor 0s that required removal
Notes_timeFormat: temporal data provided as years. The only modification to this field involved converting to a numeric object.

Notes_siteFormat: Sites have a lot of  information including net mesh size, some species or catch information, and several number combinations. No lat_longs. No changes made to site data, need to find metdata for info on site coding
Notes_spFormat: no bad spp to remove, nothing changed in species field.
Notes_countFormat: Data represents abundance count. There were no NAs nor 0s that required removal.  Count data is not in whole numbers, must be concentrations or densities per a certain volume of seawater
Notes_timeFormat: data provided as years. only modification to this field was converting to numeric object.
PropOcc_notes: Only 5 years of data present across the dataset -- proportional occurrence frame was not made.

Notes_siteFormat: Sites are written as region, location of site/siteinfo and lat_longs.  No sites removed and no changes made to data.

Notes_countFormat: Data represents count of abundance. There were no NAs nor 0s that required removal

Notes_siteFormat: site fields were just lat long, and they were concatenated.
Notes_spFormat: species entries frequently listed a paper after the species e.g. Golfingia elongata (Keferstein, 1862). The first two words were extracted from each of these to list only the scientific name.  several genus-only entries were removed because there were moany species specific entries benath that genus. Several species specific entries were consolidated into the genus-only entry of that genus if there was only one possible species.
Notes_countFormat: Data represents count. No 0s or NAs removed
Notes_timeFormat: temporal data provided as years. The only modification to this field involved converting to a numeric object.

Notes_siteFormat: Sites are all at one station called Black Sea Station but there are different numbers that may indicate site numbers.  Could not find information on this data. No changes made to site data.
Notes_spFormat: No bad species found.  No changes made to field.
Notes_countFormat: Data represents abundance counts. Some non-whole numbers, so could represent plankton density. no changes or removals necessary
Notes_timeFormat: data provided as years. only modification to this field was converting to numeric object.

Notes_siteFormat: Only two different sites in this dataset.  Lat_longs were extracted from the strings using substring because it was the only useful data.

Notes_siteFormat: only useful information was lat/long values. removed other unneccessary informaton

If there is one species under the genus-only entry, it is combined with the genus only entry, but if there is more than one species entry under a genus-only entry, the genus only entries are deleted.

Notes_siteFormat: The only useful info in site entries was the lat/longs, so those were extracted. No other changes were made.
Notes_spFormat: there were many repeated species entries with the character "Â" at the end. These were removed. Some entries that were genus-only but only had one assosciated species-only entry were consolidated into the genus-only enty. There were also a few instances where the genus-only entry needed to be deleted because there was more than one species under the genus.

Notes_siteFormat: sites are listed as USA_Atlantic_sitenumber.  Site numbers go by intervals of 0.5, so site units were separated and site numbers were rounded down to whole numbers.  Sites were then pasted back together and added back to dataset
Notes_spFormat: Several genus-only entries with multiple associated species entries were eliminated, and many single species entries under a genus entry were consolidated.
Notes_countFormat: Data represents count. There were no NAs nor 0s that required removal
Notes_timeFormat: temporal data provided as years. only modification to this field involved converting to a numeric object.

Notes_siteFormat: all sites are listed as USA_GulfOfMexico_sitenumber_lat_longs. Using read.table and then paste, extracted just the USA_GulfOfMexico_sitenumber out and used that info for site determintation.  Lat_longs no longer included.

Notes_siteFormat: site field looks like "Pacific_sitenumber_lat_long", only the lat/longs were extracted. New site field looks like "lat_long"
Notes_spFormat: several species removed because the genus-only entry had many possible species underneath. One species was combined with the corresponding genus-only entry because it was the only possible listed species under the genus. One typo (an insertion of a "?") was also fixed.
Notes_countFormat: Data represents count. There were no NAs nor 0s that required removal

Notes_siteFormat: no changes were made to raw data. sites are listed by name, and some have different number IDs.

Notes_timeFormat: temporal data provided as years. The only modification to this field involved converting to a numeric object.

Notes_siteFormat: site fields concatenated. the metadata suggests that there are 6 replicates with 7 treatments each. 5 stations are within each treatment.

Notes_siteFormat:
quadrats (sites) are potentially nested into two livestock exclosures and XY coords are provided, but this is not a 
  regular hierarhical nesting and I dont think it would be useful to analyze that way.
Notes_spFormat:
Several ambiguous groups and unidentified spp removed, three unidentified species reassigned to 
  the sole member of the genus in the dataset.
Notes_countFormat: Data represents basal cover in cm^2. There were no NAs nor 0s that required removal

Notes_siteFormat: Plot and Quadrat fields concatenated.
Notes_spFormat: All taxa not identified to species were removed, resulting in the loss of 896 records
Notes_countFormat: Data represents number of stems.
Notes_timeFormat: Date field is simply year

Notes_siteFormat: site fields concatenated. metadata suggests site-block--plot-quad describes the order of nested sites from large to small.
Notes_spFormat: several species removed. Metadata was relatively uninformative regarding what constitutes a true species sample for this study. Exploration of metadata from associated Sevilleta studies were more informative regarding which species needed to be removed. Species names are predominantly provided as Kartez codes, but not always. See: http://sev.lternet.edu/data/sev-212/5048. Some codes were identified with this pdf from White Sands: https://nhnm.unm.edu/sites/default/files/nonsensitive/publications/nhnm/U00MUL02NMUS.pdf
Notes_countFormat: Data represents cover. There were no NAs nor 0s that required removal
Notes_timeFormat: temporal data provided as dates. The only modification to this field involved converting to a date object.

Notes_siteFormat: site fields concatenated. metadata suggests site-block-treatment-plot-quad describes the order of nested sites from small to large.
Notes_spFormat: several species removed. Though Evening Grosbeak and Acadian Flycatcher were factors of the species column, there were no actual entries for those species. This is most likely because the count entries associated with each of these were either zero or trace and were removed. Two other species entries were removed: TOTAL  (ALL SPECIES) and NUMBER OF SPECIES
Notes_countFormat: Data represents count. There were many 0s, 0.0s removed. bird counts that were entered as trace (t or tr) were also deleted
Notes_timeFormat: temporal data provided as dates (years) in numerical form.

Notes_siteFormat: site fields concatenated. after looking through metadata descriptions, it seems that location_web_trap describes the order of nested sites from small to large.
Notes_spFormat: Species is coded with four letter codes, but found Sevilleta species coding here:  http://sev.lternet.edu/data/sev-008/4786. No bad species removed because all accounted for in this source. Only change made was remove extra space after one species
Notes_countFormat: no count field in this dataset, so created a dataframe using table to get frequency of species per time sample per site.
Notes_timeFormat: temporal data was provided in years and seasons separated. Seasons were listed as numbers, 1 = Spring, 2 = Summer, 3 = Fall. To keep consistent date format, I re-assigned these seasons as specific dates, making Spring = 4/1, Summer = 7/1, and Fall = 10/1. Then pasted these dates to year and made them date objects. Also, field named night was removed, after reading metadata, was not necessary.

Notes_siteFormat: sites are quadrats within a 1 ha plot.  No changes made to site data. Site data was checked for variation in number of sites sampled per year.  Varied from 99 sites to 105 sites, a negligible differece, so was ignored. There may be blank site names and other misnamed sites, but this can be ignored
Notes_spFormat: no info in metadata about species coding but not many different species so little chance for error. Only items removed were blanks and items labeled with a question mark
Notes_countFormat: data was extracted by creating table and getting frequency of each species at each time sample per each site.
Notes_timeFormat: temporal data provided as dates, but with no separation betw year, month, day values. Separated the values, pasted back together, then converted to date object.  Then added the date object to the dataset.

Notes_siteFormat: site fields concatenated. the columns that originally contained the row and column of the trap within the grid had a few values that were not legitimate (according to metadata, values should be 1-5, there were a few 0s). These bad values were removed and the row and col columns were combined as "rowcol"
Notes_spFormat: species are coded. there were two codes that were not associated with any species in the metadata ("MM" and "UN"), and they were removed
Notes_countFormat: Data represents count. There was no original count column, just one row for each individual of a species found at each site/date combination. Count column extracted. There were many 0s to remove, no NAs.
Notes_timeFormat: temporal data provided as the year directly followed by the month i.e. 199112. No days were provided in the column entries, so 01 was added as the day for each entry in order for strptime to work.

Notes_siteFormat: Site fields concatenated. Each station has 5 swaths.
Notes_spFormat:
"Young laminiariales" removed (species code 558) which could refer to any of 3 kelp species;
   two size classes of Macrocystis pyrifera lumped together
Notes_countFormat: Data represents cover. There were no NAs nor 0s that required removal
Notes_timeFormat: temporal data provided as dates. The only modification to this field involved converting to a date object.

Notes_siteFormat: site fields concatenated. metadata suggests that there are 4-5 transects within each station.
Notes_spFormat: Removed all entries of Sebastes spp. because there were multiple other entries of the Sebastes genus that were identified to the species. There were other entries with unidentified species, but each had a unique genus, so there was no overlap, so they were kept.
Notes_countFormat: Data represents density. In the raw data, adult and juvenile densities were in separate columns. These were added together in count column.
Notes_timeFormat: temporal data provided as dates. The only modification to this field involved converting to a date object.

Notes_siteFormat: site fields concatenated. metadata suggests that there are 4-5 transects within each station.
Notes_spFormat: Combined the female and male entries of Semicossyphus pulcher into species code 1006. Removed all entries of Sebastes spp. because there were multiple other entries of the Sebastes genus that were identified to the species. There were other entries with unidentified species, but each had a unique genus, so there was no overlap, so they were kept.
Notes_countFormat: Data represents density. In the raw data, adult and juvenile densities were in separate columns. These were added together in count column.
Notes_timeFormat: temporal data provided as dates. The only modification to this field involved converting to a date object.

Notes_siteFormat: site field is a concatenation of lat and long for some sites, but for others is a provided sitename. The scale of these sites is variable as this is an amalgamation of heterogeneous datasets.
Notes_spFormat: Some simple misspellings were fixed, and unidentified species ("Unknown", or e.g., "Aedes spp.") were removed.
Notes_countFormat: No 0s or NAs. Count is a count of adult individuals
Notes_timeFormat: Day, month and year combined into single date field

Notes_siteFormat: data can be analyzed at the scale of the entire "site" or at the "plot"
Notes_spFormat: All non-rodents that were not identified to species were removed based on the species table associated with this dataset.
Notes_countFormat: Each row represents the trapping of a single individual, so count=1

All taxa not identified to species were removed, except those reflecting particular
